      <div class="callout" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        <div class="callout-label">Recommendation</div>
        <p>The recommended platform is Microsoft Forms, which integrates natively with the M365 ecosystem and lets board members respond without creating an account or logging in. Each submission triggers an automated workflow that generates a clean, one-page PDF summary of the full response and delivers it by email, eliminating any manual export or formatting work.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="step-block">
        <div class="step-label">Tool Stack</div>
        <div class="step-text"><strong>Microsoft Forms</strong> (collection) → <strong>Word template on OneDrive</strong> (one-page response layout) → <strong>Power Automate</strong> (populate template, convert to PDF, send email) → <strong>Outlook</strong> (internal email delivery)</div>
      </div>

      <div class="rule"></div>

      <p><strong style="font-weight:500; color:var(--burgundy);">How the Workflow Runs</strong></p>

      <div class="steps-list" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        <div class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num">1</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <strong>Collection — Microsoft Forms</strong>
            <p>Respondent submits via a shared form link. No account or login required. Responses are captured instantly and stored in the connected M365 environment.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num">2</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <strong>Layout — Word Template on OneDrive</strong>
            <p>Each answer is mapped into a structured Word template stored in OneDrive, producing a consistent one-page "Survey Response" layout per submission.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num">3</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <strong>Automation — Power Automate</strong>
            <p>Power Automate converts the completed template to PDF and emails it to the designated internal recipient inbox on a per-response basis. Summaries arrive within minutes of completion and are easy to forward or archive.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step-item">
